attributes.description: Determines the Alert's color scheme & Icon based on its purpose.

attributes.name: visible
attributes.description: Whether the Alert is visible or hidden.

attributes.name: message
attributes.description:
Message/content displayed within the Alert's body (accepts HTML).
If message Prop is undefined, Alert will render a "message" named slot.

attributes.name: dismissible
attributes.description:
When true, Alert will display a "close" button that will dismiss/
hide the Alert when clicked. NOTE: only available for "info" &
"success" severity levels (i.e. "warning" & "error" Alerts are NOT
dismissible per UX standards).

attributes.name: timeout
attributes.description: How long after the alert renders should it stay on screen? (ms).

attributes.name: loading
attributes.description:
When true, Alert will display a "loading spinner" Icon in place
of the Icon associated with its "severity". NOTE: only available
for "info" or "success" severity levels (i.e. "warning" & "error"
Alerts cannot display as "loading" per UX standards).

attributes.name: inline
attributes.description:
If true, the Alert's width will be determined by its content
(rather than expanding to 100% width of container).

attributes.name: remove-margin
attributes.description: If true, removes Alert's bottom margin.

attributes.name: snackbar
attributes.description:
When true, Alert will be displayed as a "floating" element (i.e.
appears on top of page content) in the position specified by the
"position" Prop. NOTE: use the "width" & "position" Props to
customize the "snackbar" Alert's appearance, & use the "timeout"
Prop to automatically hide Alert after a specified time limit.

attributes.name: position
attributes.description:
When "snackbar" Prop is true, determines "floating" position of the
Alert relative to the viewport. NOTE: this Prop ONLY applies to
"snackbar" Alerts & will be ignored if "snackbar" Prop is false.

attributes.name: z-index
attributes.description: Overrides default CSS z-index value for snackbar.

attributes.name: width
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED: "width" is now deprecated. "snackbar" Alerts
are now responsive based on viewport size & "message" length.
If this Prop is used, Alert will NOT be responsive --
When "snackbar" Prop is true, defines the Alert's width. NOTE:
this Prop ONLY applies to "snackbar" Alerts & will be ignored
if "snackbar" Prop is false.

attributes.description:
The label text displayed on the Button OR the "aria-label" applied
to Icon-Only Buttons. NOTE: when using the "icon" Prop, you should
still provide a descriptive label to this Prop for accessibility.

attributes.name: type
attributes.description:
Sets the color & style of the Button. NOTE: "primary" Buttons should
be used very sparingly, & should only be used for the most important
actions in the user's workflow (i.e. you should NOT have 2+ "primary"
Buttons side-by-side).

attributes.name: color-scheme
attributes.description:
NOTE: This Prop applies to Icon-Only Buttons (i.e. "icon" Prop) &
"type: ghost" Buttons ONLY (it will be ignored for all other Button
types). Sets color of Button's label text and/or embedded Icon to
"light" or "dark" for increased contrast when displayed on a color
background. For example, if your Button is displayed on a DARK BLUE
background, set this Prop's value to "light" so that the label color
will be white (instead of the default blue). If your Button is
displayed on a YELLOW background, set this Prop's value to "dark" so
that the label will be dark gray (instead of the default blue). Do
NOT change this Prop's value if your Button is displayed on a WHITE
background. See "Examples" tab for more info.

should have the same height as the form field.

color from the parent component / element.

Button Group will automatically select the first non-disabled option
in the "options" array IF no other selected option is defined (i.e.
the "selectedLabel" Prop, the "selectedValue" Prop, or an option

attributes.name: card-title
attributes.description:
When provided, Card will render a header section that displays this Prop's
value as the Card's title. NOTE: if this Prop is omitted, Card will NOT render
a header section, will NOT be collapsible, & will NOT display an action button
or Badge.

attributes.name: title-label
attributes.description:
When provided, adds an optional label/prefix before the "cardTitle" text
in Card's header & automatically makes the "cardTitle" text bold (see
Card's usage examples for a demo). NOTE: "cardTitle" Prop is required
for this Prop to be functional.

attributes.name: subtitle
attributes.description:
When provided, displays an optional "subtitle" underneath the "cardTitle"
text in Card's header. Subtitle text will be smaller & lighter than
"cardTitle" text, & is meant to provide additional context. NOTE:
"cardTitle" Prop is required for this Prop to be functional.

attributes.name: full-height
attributes.description: When true, Card will expand to be 100% of its parent container's height.

attributes.name: border
attributes.description: Whether the Card has an outer border. Overrides theme-specific default.

attributes.name: drop-shadow
attributes.description: Whether the Card has a drop shadow. Overrides theme-specific default.

attributes.name: collapsible
attributes.description:
When true, Card body will be collapsible. Card can be expanded/
collapsed by clicking the "up/down chevron" button, clicking the
Card title, or changing the "collapsed" Prop value. NOTE: "cardTitle"
Prop is required for this Prop to be functional.

attributes.name: collapsed
attributes.description:
Controls whether collapsible Card is currently expanded/collapsed.
This Prop can be used after initial load/render to dynamically expand
or collapse Card. NOTE: "collapsible" Prop MUST be true AND "cardTitle"
Prop must be provided for this Prop to be functional.

attributes.name: remove-content-padding
attributes.description:
When true, Card body & "action-set" slot will NOT have internal
top/bottom/left/right padding.

attributes.name: remove-vertical-content-padding
attributes.description:
When true, Card body & "action-set" slot will NOT have internal
top/bottom padding.

attributes.name: remove-header-border
attributes.description:
When true, Card will NOT render a border beneath its header section.
NOTE: "cardTitle" Prop is required for this Prop to be functional.

attributes.name: remove-margin
attributes.description: When true, removes Card's default bottom margin.

attributes.name: action-text
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED: "actionText" is now deprecated. Instead, use the "label"
property of the "actionButtonConfig" Prop. -- When defined, renders
an "action button" in the Card header that displays this Prop's
value as its label. By default, the "action button" will also
display an "external link" Icon next to the label - the Icon can
be customized using the "actionIcon" Prop.

attributes.name: is-new
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED: "isNew" is now deprecated. Instead, use the "label"
property of the "badgeConfig" Prop. -- If the card houses something
new, such as a feature, or info, should we render a 'New!' Badge?

attributes.name: refreshable
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED: "refreshable" is now deprecated. Instead, add an
Icon-Only FLUID Button with "refresh" Icon to Card's "header" slot.
-- Indicates that Card has the ability to be refreshed - when true,
Card will render a "refresh button" adjacent to the Card title.

attributes.name: refresh-tooltip
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED: "refreshTooltip" is now deprecated. Instead, add an
Icon-Only FLUID Button with "refresh" Icon & "popoverConfig"
to Card's "header" slot. -- If "refreshable" Prop is true, adds
an optional Popover to the "refresh button" (i.e. this Prop sets
the Popover's "message" Prop value).

attributes.name: refresh-tooltip-placement
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED: "refreshTooltipPlacement" is now deprecated. Popover's
built-in edge detection will prevent it from appearing offscreen,
making this Prop unnecessary. -- If "refreshable: true", sets the
embedded Popover's placement in relation to the "refresh" Icon.

attributes.name: refreshing
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED: "refreshing" is now deprecated. Instead,
When true, indicates that the Card is currently refreshing (i.e. if
the calling component is refreshing, this should be true).

reflect the form element's current state - it can be used as a
"synchronous" alternative to the public async "getValue()" method.

attributes.name: supplementary-label

attributes.name: help-text
attributes.description:
If provided, Combo Box's Form Label will render a "helptext" icon
with attached Popover. To render a basic Popover with default
Prop values, simply provide the Popover's message as a string
value to this Prop. To render a Popover with customized Props,
provide a FluidPopoverConfig object to this Prop with the "message"
property set. For more information, please see Popover's API
documentation.

attributes.name: inline-field
attributes.description: Removes the form field's default bottom margin.

attributes.name: allow-cancel
attributes.description:

attributes.name: disable-auto-highlight

attributes.name: dynamic-menu-width
attributes.description:
When true, Combo Box's dropdown menu will dynamically expand its
width based on the text content of its options (i.e. the menu's
width is allowed to extend past the edge of the component). When
false, the dropdown menu's width will match the overall width of
the component, regardless of the size of its options. NOTE: this

attributes.name: auto-focus
attributes.description:
If true, this field will automatically have focus on page load.

attributes.name: empty-list-message

percentages, decimal numbers between 0 and 1 equate to percent

should contain valid CSS units - i.e. 'px', '%', 'em', 'vh', etc.).

attributes.name: max-height
attributes.description:
The maximum height of the Container. FluidSize values equate to preset
percentages, decimal numbers between 0 and 1 equate to percent
values, whole numbers greater than 1 equate to pixel values, and
strings are outputted directly as inline style values (NOTE: strings
should contain valid CSS units - i.e. 'px', '%', 'em', 'vh', etc.).

attributes.name: overflow-x
attributes.description:
How the Container should handle horizontal content overflow. NOTE: setting
this Prop to 'hidden' or 'scroll' WILL cause absolutely-position elements
(e.g. FLUID Popover, FLUID Dropdown Button, etc.) that overflow the container
bounds to be truncated.

attributes.name: overflow-y
attributes.description:
How the Container should handle vertical content overflow. NOTE: setting
this Prop to 'hidden' or 'scroll' WILL cause absolutely-position elements
(e.g. FLUID Popover, FLUID Dropdown Button, etc.) that overflow the container
bounds to be truncated.

attributes.name: padding
attributes.description:
Padding applied to the body of the Container. FluidSize values equate
to preset pixel values, decimal numbers between 0 and 1 equate to percent
values, whole numbers greater than 1 equate to pixel values, and
strings are outputted directly as inline style values (NOTE: strings
should contain valid CSS units - i.e. 'px', '%', 'em', 'vw', etc.). Strings
can contain CSS shorthand to set padding on individual sides of the Container
(e.g. '1em 2em 3em 4em' would set 1em padding on Container top, 2em padding on
Container right, 3em padding on Container bottom, & 4em padding on Container left).

attributes.name: margin
attributes.description:
Margin applied to Container element. FluidSize values equate to preset
pixel values, decimal numbers between -1 and 1 equate to negative/positive
percent values, whole numbers less than -1 or greater than 1 equate to
negative/positive pixel values, and strings are outputted directly as inline style
values (NOTE: strings should contain valid CSS units - i.e. 'px', '%', 'em', 'vw',
etc.). Strings can contain CSS shorthand to set margin on individual sides of the
Container (e.g. '1em 2em 3em 4em' would set 1em margin on Container top, 2em margin on
Container right, 3em margin on Container bottom, & 4em margin on Container left).

for example, justify and alignItems are reversed when used with column.

(viewport sizes: >0px). Accepts number value 1-12, "auto", or "fill".
NOTE: when setting breakpoint sizes larger than "colSm", it's
recommended to ALWAYS set this Prop's value to 12 - this provides

breakpoints will behave as if no "col-..." Prop is set).

attributes.name: col-sm
attributes.description:
Sets column width at large mobile / small tablet breakpoint size & up
(viewport sizes: 480px). Accepts number value 1-12, "auto", or "fill".

attributes.name: col-md
attributes.description:
Sets column width at tablet / small desktop breakpoint size & up
(viewport sizes: 768px). Accepts number value 1-12, "auto", or "fill".

attributes.name: col-lg
attributes.description:
Sets column width at desktop breakpoint size & up
(viewport sizes: 992px). Accepts number value 1-12, "auto", or "fill".

attributes.name: col-xl
attributes.description:
Sets column width at large desktop breakpoint size & up
(viewport sizes: 1200px). Accepts number value 1-12, "auto", or "fill".

attributes.name: auto
attributes.description:
Sets column width automatically based on content width at ALL
breakpoint sizes (i.e. "fluid" column width - no pun intended ).
To use "auto width" at specific breakpoint sizes, set any of the

attributes.name: align-self

attributes.name: size

attributes.name: color

attributes.name: rotate

attributes.name: flip-vertical

attributes.name: inline

attributes.name: scale
attributes.description:

are in multiples of 5 and correspond to a percentage reduction. If you find you
need to scale up, use the next size up and scale down accordingly.

attributes.name: popover-config

attributes.name: initial-value

Default value to be displayed within Input Field's <input> on first
load. NOTE: this Prop is NOT dynamically updated after initial load
like the "value" Prop is, & cannot be used to update the form field's
value after the first render.

attributes.name: value

The Input Field's current value. This Prop is dynamically updated to
reflect the form field's current state, so it can be used as a
"synchronous" alternative to the public async "getValue()" method.
If provided on first load, populates the form field with a default

update the form field's value (similar to "setValue()" method). NOTE:

are provided.

attributes.name: supplementary-label

attributes.name: placeholder

attributes.name: disabled

attributes.name: readonly

attributes.name: help-text

with attached Popover. To render a basic Popover with default

value to this Prop. To render a Popover with customized Props,

property set. For more information, please see Popover's API
documentation.

attributes.name: inline-field

attributes.name: allow-cancel

clicked. The field's <input> must have a value for button to be
visible. Button is NOT displayed when field has "required" validation.

attributes.name: auto-focus

When true, this field will automatically have focus on page load.
Note: only one form field should have "autoFocus" set to true
on a page. Multiple fields with "autoFocus: true" can/will cause

attributes.name: max-length

in the form field's <input>. NOTE: does not apply to number fields
(i.e. "type" Prop is "number").

attributes.name: step

standard <a> element (anchor tag) & navigation should NOT be
handled by the consuming application's router. Sets the URL to

attributes.name: route
attributes.description:
NOTE: use this Prop INSTEAD OF "href" when navigation should be
handled by the consuming application's router (i.e. equivalent to
Angular's "routerLink" or React's <Link to="...">). Sets the route
to be emitted via the "linkClicked" Event when the Link is clicked.

attributes.name: inline
attributes.description:
When true, Link will be styled as an inline element with regular
font weight & an underline. When false (default), Link will be
styled as a "standalone" element (i.e. display: flex;) with bold
font weight & no underline (except on :hover). Inline styles
should be used for Links within text blocks or Tables.

attributes.name: center
attributes.description:
When true, Link will appear center-aligned within its container.
NOTE: this Prop cannot be used when "inline" Prop is true.

attributes.name: target
attributes.description:
Specifies where to open the Link. "_blank" opens the link in a new
window or tab. "_self" opens the link in the same frame as it was
clicked (default). "_parent" opens the link in the parent frame.
"_top" opens the link in the full body of the window.

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: When true, Link will be disabled.

attributes.name: type
attributes.description:
If Link is an email address or phone number, specifies the Link's
behavior when clicked. "email" will add a "mailto:" prefix to the
Link's "href" attribute, & will open the user's native email client
when clicked. "tel" will add a "tel:" prefix to the Link's "href"
attribute, & will open the user's native phone or VoIP application
when clicked. NOTE: this Prop MUST be used with the "href" Prop
(NOT the "route" Prop).

attributes.name: color-scheme
attributes.description:
Sets a Link's text color
to "light" or "dark" for increased contrast when displayed on a color
background. For example, if your Link is displayed on a DARK
BLUE background, set this Prop's value to "light" so that the text
color will be white (instead of the default blue). If your
Link is displayed on a YELLOW background, set this Prop's value to
"dark" so that the label will be dark gray (instead of the default
blue). Do NOT change this Prop's value if your Link is
displayed on a WHITE background.

attributes.name: link
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED: "link" is now deprecated. Instead, use "href" Prop for
standard <a> tag functionality, or use "route" Prop for navigation
handled by the consuming application's router. -- The URL / route to
navigate to when the Link is clicked. When "useNative" Prop is TRUE,
this Prop's value must be a valid URL. When "useNative" Prop is FALSE,
navigation will NOT occur automatically & will need to be handled
via the consuming application's router.

attributes.name: use-native

browser to the configured link (i.e. via "href" attr). Set to false
to handle routing internally.

Sets the overall size of the Loading Spinner. Accepts all FluidSize
values EXCEPT "xxs" & "full".

attributes.name: circle-type
attributes.description: Sets the Loading Spinner's aesthetic style & animation behavior.

attributes.name: centered
attributes.description: If true, Spinner will be horizontally centered within its container.

attributes.name: vertical-padding
attributes.description:
Sets top & bottom padding of Loading Spinner container. If provided,
overrides default 1em top/bottom padding. FluidSize values equate
to preset pixel values, decimal numbers between 0 and 1 equate to percent
values, whole numbers greater than 1 equate to pixel values, and
strings are outputted directly as inline style values (NOTE: strings
should contain valid CSS units - i.e. 'px', '%', 'em', 'vh', etc.).

attributes.name: loading-message
attributes.description: If provided, displays a message string beneath the Loading Spinner.

attributes.name: container
attributes.description:
NOTE: this Prop MUST be used in conjunction with the "loading" Prop.
When true, Loading Spinner will be rendered as a container for slotted
content (i.e. enables Loading Spinner's slot). As long as the "loading"
Prop is true, the Spinner will be displayed on top of its slotted content
& all child elements will be inaccessible. When the "loading" Prop is
false (or undefined), the Spinner will be hidden & all slotted children
will be accessible (i.e. Loading Spinner becomes a standard <div>).

attributes.name: height
attributes.description:
When loading spinner is used as a blocking container, us this prop to set
a minimum pixel height for the blocking spinner, so it can take up an
appropriate amount of space on your page until whatever content you are loading
can be loaded.

attributes.name: muted
attributes.description:
If true, the loading spinner will be a smaller, more muted spinner. This is
useful for inline loading spinners, where the standard size and colour may be
too much for the container.

attributes.name: loading
attributes.description:
When true, Spinner will be visible & slotted content will be blocked /
inaccessible. When false, Spinner will NOT be displayed, & slotted child
elements WILL be accessible (see "container" Prop documentation for more
info). NOTE: if "container" Prop is FALSE, this Prop is OPTIONAL & will
NOT affect the Spinner's visibility if undefined (i.e. Spinner will always
be visible until removed from the DOM). However, if "container" Prop is
TRUE, this Prop is REQUIRED to display the Spinner (i.e. Spinner will
NOT be visible if this Prop is left undefined).

attributes.name: spinner-id
attributes.description:
Set a unique spinner ID. If there are multiple spinners on a single page,
this can be useful when dynamically toggling their loading state.

attributes.name: z-index
attributes.description: Overrides default CSS z-index value for Loading Spinner container.

slots.description: Content that is loading. All children of this slot will be inaccessible while "loading" Prop is true. NOTE: "container" Prop MUST be true to enable this slot. See documentation for "container" & "loading" Props for more information.

attributes.description:

of translucent.

attributes.name: outside-click-close
attributes.description:
When true, clicking anywhere outside the Modal body container
(i.e. anywhere on the backdrop overlay) will close it. NOTE: If
your Modal requires users to complete an action/task before close,
you should set this Prop to false.

attributes.name: actions-disabled
attributes.description:
When true, all action buttons will be disabled EXCEPT for those
with "enableOnModalDisabled" property set to true. NOTE: If you need
a Modal to complete an action before closing, set this to true while
that action completes.

attributes.name: should-disable-close
attributes.description:
Disables Modal's "close" button IF this Prop is true AND
"actionsDisabled" Prop is true as well (i.e. both Props must be true
for "close" button to be disabled).

attributes.name: hide-close-icon
attributes.description:
When true, removes Modal's "close" button. NOTE: This should be used
with caution - if you haven't set up a "close" action button with
corresponding event listener OR enabled "outsideClickClose", you
won't be able to close the Modal!

attributes.name: limit-overflow
attributes.description:
When TRUE, limits Modal's max-height to 70% & allows internal
scrolling within the Modal's body, but also truncates any content
that overflows the edges of the Modal container (such as Popovers).
When FALSE, Modal's height will be dictated by the height of its
content, and content WILL be allowed to display outside the Modal
container edges without truncation (see usage examples).

on the filter menu - this helps improve performance on large datasets.

attributes.description:
If the table is stateful, modifications to filters/visible columns/sorting etc.
are stored locally to keep the table state on return visits (defaults to false);

attributes.name: expanded-button-position
attributes.description:
Overrides default position of each row's "expand" button (rendered when
"expandableForm" or "expandableRowTemplate" Props used). By default,
the "expandableForm" Prop will render the "expand" buttons on the LEFT side
of the Table (e.g. "right" will override the default position). The
"expandableRowTemplate" Prop will render the "expand" buttons on the
RIGHT side of the Table by default (i.e. "left" will override the
default position).

attributes.name: use-renderer
attributes.description:
If an expandable form template is given, set this to true if your configuration returns
a FluidComponentDefinition and the table will use component renderer to render it.

attributes.name: max-height
attributes.description:
Sets a maximum height for the displayed table, if there is still visible data
beyond the maximum height, the table will become scrollable.

attributes.name: sticky-headers
attributes.description:
When true, Table headers will be "sticky" on vertical scroll. NOTE:
Table MUST have a maximum height defined (i.e. "maxHeight" Prop) for
this Prop to function.

attributes.name: data-loading
attributes.description:
Lets the table know if data from above is loading (from an API for example) so that
it can show a loading spinner until it has the data (Must be managed from consuming
application)

attributes.name: refresh-delay
attributes.description:
When the dataItems array is changed, the table enters a 'refresh' state - this is to ensure all the
operations the table has to carry out on the new data set can complete before rendering the table nodes.
This value determines how long the table is in that refresh state, so it can be fine-tuned if there any
issues with larger, or more complex datasets.

attributes.name: allow-overflow
attributes.description:
If true, horizontal scrolling will be allowed on tables with many columns. NB - If allowOverflow is true,
horizontal scrolling will be enabled, however, filter menu style will be switched to compact to prevent overflow on the Y axis from cutting off the view.

attributes.name: track-form-state
attributes.description:
If true, the table emit the form state of each nested form for each change - if you do not need
to know the forms state (validity, etc) prior to hitting the save button (and receiving mutations),
you can set this to false to improve performance.

attributes.name: striped
attributes.description:
If true, Table rows will be styled with "zebra stripes" (alternating rows
will have gray background).

attributes.name: row-borders
attributes.description: If true, each Table row will have a bottom border.

attributes.name: disable-column-visibility
attributes.description: If true, disables the column visibility filters

attributes.name: handle-delete
attributes.description:
If true, the table will provide the ability to delete a row, without
having to supplement with a defined action.

attributes.name: commit-on-valid-save
attributes.description:
If true (default), a table with an expandable form or editable field, and
table-rendered edit actions with automatically commit the changes to the forms
to its own internal memory on click of the Save button if the forms are valid.

This will fire the dataMutated event, which lets the consuming application know
the new data set values.

attributes.name: validate-on-save
attributes.description:
Where a table has nested forms or editable cells with validation configured, the table
will not emit a dataMutated event when the save button is clicked unless all are valid.
When this prop is set to true, the table will validate the cells when save is clicked and
cells are not valid, offering immediate visual feedback to the user.

attributes.name: actions-disabled
attributes.description: If true, the save and cancel buttons will be disabled.

attributes.name: row-identifier
attributes.description:

identify the item, this property tells the table to use it rather than generated
IDs

attributes.name: disabled

to be explicitly set to false if we don't want pagination

(instead of a "block" element) with right padding (for spacing
between consecutive inline elements).

attributes.name: align-super

When true, applies "super" vertical alignment (i.e. superscript
format) to the text.

attributes.name: block
attributes.description:
When true, FLUID Text will be displayed as a "block" element. NOTE: this Prop is only applicable when "strong" Prop is true (default FLUID Text renders an embedded

tag, which is already a "block" element).

attributes.name: italics

attributes.name: center
attributes.description: When true, text will be center-aligned.

attributes.name: muted
attributes.description: When true, text will be slightly smaller & will have a lighter color.

attributes.name: disable-gutters
attributes.description: Removes default top & bottom margins when true.

attributes.name: disable-padding
attributes.description:
When true, removes right padding from inline FLUID Text. NOTE:
this Prop is only applicable when "inline" Prop is true (default
FLUID Text has top/bottom margin instead of padding).

attributes.name: disable-gutter
attributes.description:
Removes top OR bottom margin when provided. To remove both, use
"disableGutters" Prop. Accepts "top" or "bottom".

attributes.name: color
attributes.description: Optional color for the text, otherwise, inherits from parent.

attributes.name: align
attributes.description: Sets text alignment to left (default), right, or center.

attributes.name: preserve-spacing
attributes.description:
When true, sequences of white space will be preserved (including tabs), & lines will be broken at newline characters &
(i.e. applies "white-space: pre-wrap" CSS rule). This overrides the default behavior where newline characters, spaces, & tabs are collapsed/removed.

attributes.name: small
attributes.description: When true, font size will 12.5% smaller.

attributes.name: break-word
attributes.description:
When true, character strings that are normally "unbreakable" (such
as long words or URLs) are allowed to be broken at arbitrary points if
there are no other acceptable break points in the line.

attributes.name: text-overflow
attributes.description:
Sets overflow behavior when text width is greater than the component's
width. By default, FLUID Text will wrap overflowing content onto new
line(s). Setting this Prop to "clip" will truncate text overflow
mid-character, and "ellipsis" will truncate text overflow with "..."
(NOTE: these values should only be used when seeing the entire text
is NOT necessary to understand the content's context/purpose). Both
"clip" & "ellipsis" values will display a tooltip on :hover containing
the full, unedited content.

DEPRECATED: "wrap" is now deprecated. Instead, use "preserveSpacing" Prop (same functionality, just a different naming convention) -- When true, sequences of white space will be preserved (including tabs), & lines will be broken at newline characters &

events.name: pageChanged
events.description:
Event fired when a new page is selected within Paginator.
Emits the derived FluidPaginationState object.

events.name: popoverToggled
events.description:
Event emitted when Popover is opened or closed. Emits "true" when
Popover is opened & "false" when closed.

events.name: valueChange
events.description: Emits the element state when its value changes

events.name: valueChange
events.description: Emits the element state when its value changes.

events.name: search
events.description: Emits when the search button has been clicked

events.name: searchTermUpdated
events.description: Emits when the search term is updated

events.name: selected
events.description:
Emits the FluidOption value of the selected option
accessible from $event.detail

events.name: selectionCleared
events.description:
Emits whenever the selection was cleared with the cancel
icon - { payload: FluidOption } - the option that was cleared.

events.name: valueChange
events.description: Emits the entire element state for the element

events.name: sidebarToggled
events.description:
Event emitted when Sidebar is opened or closed. The event's payload
is a boolean value that indicates its "visible" status. At desktop
size, this event is only emitted when the "collapsible" Prop is true.

events.name: statusChanged
events.description: Event emitted when the property `status` was changed.

events.name: titleChanged
events.description: Event emitted when the property `title` was changed.

events.name: hiddenChanged
events.description: Event emitted when the property `hidden` was changed.

events.name: finished
events.description:
Emits `true` or `false` to know if the stepper was finished.
Checks if all the steps don't have an error status.

events.name: stepChanged
events.description: Emits the active step when the step is changed.

events.name: disableChanged
events.description: Event emitted when the property `disabled` was changed.

events.name: titleChanged
events.description: Event emitted when the property `title` was changed.

events.name: hiddenChanged
events.description: Event emitted when the property `hidden` was changed.

events.name: actionClicked
events.description:
Emits the row actionKey that was clicked, along with the rowData from
the row that was clicked

events.name: cellClicked
events.description: Emits the cell data whenever a cell is clicked

events.name: formActionClicked
events.description:
Emits when one of the form actions is clicked, in case the parent component
has any external validations etc to do

events.name: editableCellChange
events.description:
Emits whenever an editable cell changes value. Emits the new value, along with the
row data for the row it changed on.

events.name: dataMutated
events.description:
Emits when the tables 'Save' action is clicked. Emits both the new, now
updated dataset, along with a list of mutated rows. This allows the
consuming component to intercept changes and decide whether to commit
the change, or to reset the data;

events.name: formValueChanged
events.description: Fired whenever an element in a nested form value changes

events.name: nestedFormState
events.description: Emits when the state of the nested forms changes.

events.name: groupToggled
events.description: Emits when the expansion state of a group is toggled.

events.name: groupsToggled
events.description: Emits the group state when all are expanded/collapsed

events.name: tableSearched
events.description: Emits whenever the table search is executed

events.name: tableSorted
events.description: Emits whenever the table is sorted

events.name: tableFiltered
events.description: Emits whenever the table is filtered

events.name: columnVisibility
events.description: Emits whenever the table column visibility has changed.

events.name: expansionToggled
events.description: Emits whenever a table row is expanded.

events.name: tabChanged
events.description:
Event emitted when a Tab is clicked, regardless of whether the selected
Tab changes.

events.name: tabHasChanged
events.description: Event emitted when a Tab is clicked that changes the selected Tab.

events.name: valueChange
events.description:
Emits the element state when the form field's value changes (i.e.
fired on every keystroke).

events.name: valueChange
events.description: Emits the element state when its value changes

events.name: toggleState
events.description:
Emits the state of the Toggle Group with each Toggle change.
The emitted element takes the form of an object such that each
key is the `controlName`, and the value is the value of the Toggle.

{ <controlName>: <toggleValue> }

events.name: tourStopped
events.description: Emits when the tour is stopped and at what step number (0 indexed).

events.name: menuItemClick
events.description:
Event fired when a menu item with no submenu is clicked. Contains
the FluidMenuItem that was clicked.

events.name: submenuButtonClick
events.description:
Event fired when a menu item with a submenu is clicked. Contains
the FluidMenuItem that was clicked.
